Step1:

In user-detail.php

<a href="../functions/removeuser.php" class="btn btn-sm btn-danger float-right">
                            <i class="fas fa-pen"></i> Remove Customer
                        </a>

Step2:

Create a php file in functions folder and name it removeuser.php and paste the code

<?php
session_start();

if (!isset($_SESSION['loggedin'])) {
    header('Location: login.php');
    exit;
}

$customer = $_SESSION['customer'];
include 'db.php';

removeUser($customer);

?>

Step3:

In db.php file paste the following code

// Remove User 
function removeUser($customer)
{
    global $db;
    $query = "UPDATE `customer` SET `status` = 'inactive'";
    echo $query;
    $result = $db->query($query);

    if (!$result) {
        echo 'Error updating info.';
    } else {
        header('Location: ../Pages/users.php');
        exit;
    }
}


Step4:

Fix the searching query on user page based on status.
